headlines.description: O'Showen Williams scored a career-best 20 points and Ronshad Shabazz added 19 with three steals as Appalachian State pulled away in the second half for an 81-66 win over Coastal Carolina in Sun Belt Conference action on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Appalachian St. closes strong, tops Coastal Carolina 81-66

headlines.description: TJ Haws scored 26 points with seven assists, Yoeli Childs had 20 points and nine rebounds and BYU beat San Francisco 75-73 in overtime on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haws hits winning FTs, BYU beats San Francisco 75-73 in OT

headlines.description: Otis Livingston II scored 14 points, Jaire Grayer added 12 points and 12 rebounds and George Mason held off George Washington for a 72-65 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: George Mason holds off George Washington, wins 72-65

headlines.description: Johnathan Stove had a career-best 28 points and Bryce Washington added 18 with 13 rebounds as Louisiana recovered from its only Sun Belt Conference loss by getting past Georgia Southern 102-91 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisiana recovers from only league loss, beats Ga. Southern

headlines.description: Jermaine Marrow totaled 27 points, six rebounds and six assists to lead Hampton to an 82-52 wire-to-wire victory over Norfolk State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marrow leads Hampton to 82-52 romp over Norfolk State

headlines.description: Tyler Sharpe hit two 3-pointers in the closing minutes Saturday night to secure Northern Kentucky's fifth straight win, an 86-80 victory over Green Bay that moved the Norse into sole possession of first-place in the Horizon League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northern Kentucky takes Horizon lead, beats Green Bay 86-80

headlines.description: Jordan Giles scored 23 points, Broderick Robinson had 17 points and a season-high 11 rebounds and Missouri-Kansas City beat Utah Valley 77-70 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giles, Robinson lead UMKC past Utah Valley 77-70

headlines.description: Shakur Juiston scored 22 points and grabbed 14 rebounds and UNLV beat Wyoming 85-70 on Saturday night.
Tyree Appleby and Stefan Kenic converted 7 of 8 from the free-throw line in the final two minutes and Chicago State held on to upset Illinois-Chicago, 86-78 in a Horizon League game Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cleveland State holds off UIC late to post 86-78 upset win

headlines.description: Chris Cokley had 15 points and nine rebounds and UAB rallied from nine down with less than four minutes to go for a 61-56 win on Saturday night.

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "I’m getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. It’s a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how I’m going to dictate how my team wins. … It’s a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... It’s a process. Right now, it’s tough."
